The paper deals with coding theory and analysis of codes using Fourier analysis, which are topics typically found in information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of Gowers norm and polynomials also suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the construction of codes, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
